The '''Mitsuoka Ryoga''' is a sedan manufactured by [[Mitsuoka]]. There are two versions of it, a wagon and a sedan.<ref name=ama>{{cite web|url=http://specs.amayama.com/mitsuoka/ryoga/|title=Mitsuoka Ryoga|publisher=Amayama|date=|accessdate=27 June 2014}}</ref> It has a fuel tank capacity of 60L.<ref name=yan /> The price of the Ryoga ranges from 2,461,000 yen to 2,871,750 yen.<ref name=googoo2>{{cite web|url= http://www.goo-net-exchange.com/catalog/MITSUOKA__RYOGA/|title=Mitsuoka Ryoga catalog|publisher=GooNetExchange|date=|accessdate=30 June 2014}}</ref>

==First generation==

When the Ryoga was first released in 1998, it was based on the Nissan Primera and had a 1.8L or 2.0L engine. The 1.8L engine produced 125 hp. The 2.0L engine produced 150 hp.<ref name=rus2 />

==Second generation==

When the car entered its second generation, the car became based on the Nissan Sunny. This changed the engine size to 1.5L. This 1.5L engine produces 105 hp.<ref name=rus1>{{cite web|url=http://mitsuoka.drom.ru/ryoga/|title=Mitsuoka Ryoga (<U+041C><U+0438><U+0446><U+0443><U+043E><U+043A><U+0430> <U+0420><U+0451><U+0433><U+0430>)|date=|accessdate=27 June 2014}}</ref><ref name=rus2 /> The Sunny based Ryoga has a top speed of 177 km/h and a 0-100 km/h time of 13.1 seconds. It is classified as a low emission vehicle.<ref name= rus2 />

==Trim levels==
There are two trim levels. Royal, which has slightly better equipment and Deluxe.<ref name=rus1 /> During the 2000 model year there was a larger limited edition with a 1998cc engine. There were two more limited editions in 2004. During that year Mitsuoka released a Soft Leather Edition and a Final Model edition.<ref name=googoo2 />

